The paper discusses the use of machine learning and pattern recognition approaches in the analysis of neuroimaging data for clinical applications. This falls under the intersection of computer science and neuroscience, with a focus on machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE) for classification and pattern recognition. The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in this context. Finally, the paper emphasizes the importance of considering human-computer interaction (cs.HC) in the development of effective neuroimaging data processing pipelines.
